Meanwhile, Maria Sharapova and Petra Kvitova were also knocked out in the third round.

Fourth seed Sharapova was beaten in three sets by Spain's Carla Suarez Navarro, 6-2 4-6 6-2 in a match lasting two hours and 22 minutes.

Kvitova, the world No 4 who this year won her second Wimbledon title, was seeded second in Montreal but was dumped out 6-4 1-6 6-2 by Russian Ekaterina Makarova in an even longer match clocking in at almost two hours and 40 minutes.

